---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_SUBTITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from "../consts";
import HeaderLink from "../components/HeaderLink.astro";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
    <style>
      #index-greeting {
        font-size: 1.35rem;
      }
      @media (min-width: 350px) {
        #index-greeting {
          font-size: 1.5rem;
        }
      }
      @media (min-width: 450px) {
        #index-greeting {
          font-size: 2rem;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header title={SITE_TITLE} />
    <main>
      <h1 id="index-greeting">üßë‚Äçüéì Hello, YU Student!</h1>
      <p>
        Welcome to the YU Computer Science study materials page. Here you will
        find many examples, recall questions, past papers, answers, programs,
        and much more! Although this is not an official page managed by the
        department, I nevertheless hope that you will find these materials
        useful.
      </p>
      <p>
        To get started, please click the name of the module that you want to
        study on the top nav bar. For example, if you want to study <HeaderLink>
          CS 1102
        </HeaderLink>, please click <HeaderLink href="/CS_1102">
          CS 1102
        </HeaderLink>
        on the top nav bar.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your feedback or suggestions are also welcome. My contact information is
        given at the <HeaderLink href="/about">about</HeaderLink>
        page. If you find any issue with the site or with any of the materials provided,
        please feel free to reach out :)
      </p>
